					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2"><body>
<p><font face="Verdana"><b>Everlore's Recipes to Dwarf Blacksmithing</b></font></p> 

<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">I made this chart with as much accuracy as possible. I
hope every Dwarf Blacksmith likes and can find this chart useful to them. I appreciate
all the help I received from users. If there is any information that is
incorrect or needs updating please feel free to contact me at this address <a href="mailto:Hondo@obsidian-tech.com">Korupter_(E-Marr)</a>.</font></p> 
<ul>
  <li> <b><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="http://www.everlore.com/guides.asp?ID=259466">Everlore's
    Guide
    to General Blacksmithing</a></font></b></li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p align="center"><b><font face="Verdana"><u>Everlore's Chart for Blacksmithing</u></font></b></p>
<table border="1" width="100%">


</table>
<table border="1" width="100%">
  <tr>
    <td width="100%"colspan="3">
      <p align="center"><font size="6" face="Martel">Dwarf Blacksmithing</font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="11%"><b><font face="Verdana">Skill:</font></b></td>
    <td width="21%"><b><font face="Verdana">(Armor) Makes:</font></b></td>
    <td width="68%"><b><font face="Verdana">Ingredients:</font></b></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="11%"><font face="Verdana" size="2">N/A</font></td>
    <td width="21%"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Dwarven Plate Bracer</font></td>
    <td width="68%"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Earthen Temper, Dwarven
      Smithy Hammer, Leather Backing, Brellium Chain Jointing, (1) Folded Sheets
      of Brellium, Small Plate Bracer Mold</font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="11%"><font face="Verdana" size="2">N/A</font></td>
    <td width="21%"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Dwarven Plate Vambraces</font></td>
    <td width="68%"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Earthen Temper, Dwarven
      Smithy Hammer, Leather Backing, Brellium Chain Jointing,(2) Folded Sheet
      of Brellium, Small Plate Vambraces Mold</font></td>
  </tr>
